OL,7,FClinicians have identified a gene
OL,8,Fvariant that causes a common type of
OL,9,Fhigh blood pressure, and a way to
OL,10,Fcure it.
OL,12,FA tiny benign nodule, present in one
OL,13,Fin 20 people with hypertension,
OL,14,Fproduces a hormone, aldosterone, that
OL,15,Fcontrols how much salt is in the
OL,16,Fbody. The new discovery is a gene
OL,17,Fvariant in some of these nodules
OL,18,Fwhich leads to a vast, but
OL,19,Fintermittent, over-production of the
OL,20,Fhormone.
OL,3,CScientists identify gene variant that
OL,4,Ccauses common type of high blood
OL,5,Cpressure - and a cure
